The paper deals with a problem of assigning data items to memory banks with limited capacity, which is a classic problem in computer science. The problem is motivated by the design of caching systems, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of algorithms and complexity (cs.DC) or information theory (cs.IT). The use of LP relaxation and the analysis of the running time suggest that the paper could also belong to the categories of probability and statistics (cs.PF) or systems and control (cs.SY).
